## Examples

### Good Metadata Section

```markdown
## Metadata
- **Status:** Active
- **Created:** 04-12-2025
- **Last Updated:** 04-12-2025 11:12:43 EST
- **Version:** 1.2
- **Description:** Standards for creating and structuring Cursor rules
- **Type:** Governing Standard - Defines requirements for Cursor rule creation
- **Applicability:** When creating or modifying Cursor rules
  - **Dependencies:**
    - [version-management.mdc](../../.cursor/rules/version-management.mdc) - Version numbering standards
    - [documentation-management.md](../project-planning/documentation-management.md) - Documentation management standards
- **How to Use:** Reference this standard when creating new Cursor rules or modifying existing ones
```

### Bad Metadata Section

```markdown
## Metadata
- Created: 2025-12-04
- Version: 1
```
‚ùå Problems:
- Missing Status, Last Updated, Description, Type, Applicability
- Wrong date format (should be DD-MM-YYYY)
- Missing "How to Use"
- No dependencies listed

