## How to Use This Rule

**This rule applies automatically when creating or modifying `.md` files in `docs/`, `standards/`, or `.cursor/commands/` directories.**

**Agents should:**
1. Check for metadata section at top of file
2. Verify all required fields are present
3. Update Last Updated with current EST timestamp
4. Increment version if content changed
5. Update dependencies if files are referenced
6. Ensure Status reflects current state
7. Add "How to Use" section if missing

**Validation checklist:**
- [ ] Status field present
- [ ] Created date in DD-MM-YYYY format
- [ ] Last Updated in DD-MM-YYYY HH:MM:SS EST format
- [ ] Version follows semantic versioning
- [ ] Description is clear and concise
- [ ] Type describes document and audience
- [ ] Applicability states when/where it applies
- [ ] Dependencies listed (if any)
- [ ] "How to Use" section present

---

## Notes

- **Be thorough:** Complete metadata makes documents discoverable
- **Update timestamps:** Always use EST timezone
- **Track dependencies:** Helps maintain cross-reference integrity
- **Keep Status current:** Reflects document's actual state